  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b85\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0bb5\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bcd 33 \u0b86\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc6\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bca\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bae\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b8e\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0baf\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb5\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0ba4\u0bc1 ; \u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "33 thousand metric tons of cooking gas will be available next week; Prime Minister Ranil",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "33.000 MT cooking gas is available for the country from 11th June to first week of August.",
        "Steps will be taken to get cooking gas without shortage for the next four months. Also, Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe said that we have set up a special work plan for the distribution of cooking gas in Colombo.",
        "The Prime Minister said this while replying to a question raised by a member of the ruling party, Lalith Varnakumara, during the Prime Minister's Question Time on Wednesday 6th in Parliament.",
        "As planned, after the quantity of cooking gas cylinders arrived in the country on the 9th,",
        "On July 11th or 12th, we have taken action to distribute to 140 places all over the city of Colombo.",
        "We have taken steps to distribute a total of one lakh and 40 thousand cylinders on the basis of 100 cylinders to all those places.",
        "After that we will take steps to distribute 25,000 cylinders weighing 12.5 kg daily in Colombo city.",
        "At the same time, steps will be taken to distribute cylinders to bakeries and small businesses.",
        "For this, we will take steps to distribute one lakh 12 thousand cylinders across the country from the upcoming 11th or 12th on a daily basis.",
        "We will eliminate the current gas shortage by the end of this month or early August.",
        "33 thousand metric tons of gas is available from 11th to early August. We have taken steps to distribute these to the consumers.",
        "These activities may change depending on the prevailing climate in the country and the prevailing climate at sea. However, steps will be taken to supply cooking gas without shortage for the next four months, he said."
      ],
